main event: A Naval officer spotted a glowing unidentified flying object near Keystone Heights, Florida in 1955.
interesting points: The object was visible for approximately one minute and appeared to be the size of a C-47 aircraft.
The object was observed moving from northeast to southwest.
The officer initially thought the object was a satellite but could not identify it further.
A preliminary investigation by the Naval Air Station indicated the object was likely a satellite, but no further investigative action was taken.
The report was later downgraded to unclassified for public use.
result: likely a satellite, but officially unidentified
